sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as User Browser
    participant OSRouter as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthProxy as oauth-proxy sidecar<br/>8443/TCP TLS
    participant RayDash as Ray Head Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant RayClient as Ray Client
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod<br/>10001/TCP gRPC
    participant RayWorker as Ray Worker Pod<br/>10001/TCP gRPC
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant CertInit as create-cert init container
    participant CASecret as CA Secret<br/>(ca-secret-{cluster})
    participant Controller as CodeFlare Controller
    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator
    participant Webhook as RayCluster Webhook<br/>9443/TCP TLS

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over KubeRay,Webhook: Flow 0: RayCluster Creation & Enhancement
        KubeRay->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster CR
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: Admission webhook call (mutating)
        Webhook->>Webhook: Inject oauth-proxy sidecar,<br/>mTLS init containers,<br/>TLS env vars, cert volumes
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated RayCluster spec
        K8sAPI->>Controller: RayCluster watch event
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create CA Secret (RSA 2048-bit, 1yr)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create OAuth Secret (cookie secret)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount + ClusterRoleBinding
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create OAuth Service (443→8443)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route (dashboard, reencrypt)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route (rayclient, passthrough)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicies (head + workers)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over CertInit,CASecret: Flow 3: Pod Startup - mTLS Certificate Generation
        CertInit->>K8sAPI: Read CA Secret<br/>(ServiceAccount token auth)
        K8sAPI-->>CertInit: CA key + certificate
        CertInit->>CertInit: Generate per-pod server cert<br/>via openssl (SANs: pod IP, localhost,<br/>service DNS, route hostname)
        CertInit->>CertInit: Write certs to shared volume
        Note over CertInit: RAY_USE_TLS=1 environment variable set
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over User,RayDash: Flow 1: RayCluster OAuth Dashboard Access (OpenShift)
        User->>OSRouter: GET https://ray-dashboard-{cluster}...<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        OSRouter->>OAuthProxy: Forward (reencrypt)<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        OAuthProxy->>OAuthProxy: Check OpenShift OAuth token
        alt No valid token
            OAuthProxy-->>User: 302 Redirect to OpenShift OAuth login
            User->>OAuthProxy: Return with OAuth token
        end
        OAuthProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(check pods/get permission in namespace)
        K8sAPI-->>OAuthProxy: Allowed
        OAuthProxy->>RayDash: Forward request<br/>8265/TCP HTTP (localhost)
        RayDash-->>OAuthProxy: Dashboard response
        OAuthProxy-->>OSRouter: HTTPS response
        OSRouter-->>User: Dashboard HTML
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 255)
        Note over RayClient,RayHead: Flow 2: Ray Client Connection (OpenShift)
        RayClient->>OSRouter: Connect to rayclient-{cluster}...<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS (passthrough)
        OSRouter->>RayHead: Forward (passthrough)<br/>10001/TCP gRPC mTLS
        Note over RayClient,RayHead: Auth: CA-signed client certificate
        RayHead-->>RayClient: gRPC response (mTLS)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 255, 240)
        Note over RayHead,RayWorker: Flow 3: Ray Head ↔ Worker mTLS Communication
        RayHead->>RayWorker: gRPC 10001/TCP<br/>mTLS (RAY_USE_TLS=1)<br/>CA-signed certificate
        RayWorker-->>RayHead: gRPC response<br/>mTLS (RAY_USE_TLS=1)
        RayWorker->>RayHead: gRPC 10001/TCP<br/>mTLS (RAY_USE_TLS=1)
        RayHead-->>RayWorker: gRPC response
    end
